                        Conditional rendering based on render mode
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
                    <a href="https://github.com/andrehogberg/summit-ui/blob/main/.claude/skills/render-info/SKILL.md" 
                       target="_blank" 
                       rel="noopener noreferrer"
                       class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-foreground hover:underline">
                        View on GitHub
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/>
                            <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/>
                            <line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/>
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* Skill File Format *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Skill File Format</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Skills are Markdown files with YAML frontmatter that describe the skill's purpose. The format is compatible with 
            Claude Code, OpenCode, and other AI coding assistants that support skill files.
        </p>
        <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code class="language-markdown">@skillFormatCode</code></pre>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* File Structure *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">File Structure</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Skills are organized in the <code>.claude/skills/</code> directory:
        </p>
        <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code class="language-text">@fileStructureCode</code></pre>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* How to Use *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">How to Use</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            AI coding assistants that support skills will automatically discover and use these files when working in the SummitUI repository.
        </p>
        
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border p-4">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-foreground mb-2">With Claude Code / OpenCode</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Skills are automatically loaded. When you ask the AI to run tests, it will use the <code>tunit</code> skill 
                    to understand the correct commands.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border p-4">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-foreground mb-2">With Other AI Assistants</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Reference the skill file directly in your prompt:
                    <code class="block mt-2 text-xs">"Please read .claude/skills/tunit/SKILL.md for test instructions"</code>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* Example Usage *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Example Prompts</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Here are some example prompts that will trigger skill usage:
        </p>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border p-3 bg-muted/30">
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground mb-1">Testing</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground italic">"Run the Select accessibility tests"</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1">Uses: <code>tunit</code> skill</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border p-3 bg-muted/30">
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground mb-1">Testing with filters</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground italic">"Run only the keyboard navigation tests"</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1">Uses: <code>tunit</code> skill with <code>--treenode-filter</code></p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border p-3 bg-muted/30">
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground mb-1">Render modes</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground italic">"How do I detect if the component is interactive?"</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1">Uses: <code>render-info</code> skill</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* Creating Custom Skills *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Creating Custom Skills</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            You can create your own skills for project-specific tasks. Here's how:
        </p>
        <ol class="grid gap-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground list-decimal list-inside">
            <li>Create a new directory in <code>.claude/skills/</code> with your skill name</li>
            <li>Add a <code>SKILL.md</code> file with YAML frontmatter</li>
            <li>Include the skill name and description in the frontmatter</li>
            <li>Write detailed instructions in Markdown format</li>
            <li>Include code examples and commands where helpful</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/30 p-4 mt-2">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                    <path d="M12 16v-4"/>
                    <path d="M12 8h.01"/>
                </svg>
                <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    <strong class="text-foreground">Tip:</strong> Skills work best when they're focused on a single task or topic. 
                    Create multiple small skills rather than one large skill with many responsibilities.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    @* Related Resources *@
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Related Resources</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <a href="/docs/llms" class="rounded-lg border border-border p-4 hover:bg-muted/50 transition-colors">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
